h3. Issue Summary
When trying to remove permissions from the owner in its [personal space|https://support.atlassian.com/confluence-cloud/docs/create-your-personal-space/], the action will not have effects and no messages will be displayed with the reasons for it. It is currently expected, but, a message should be displayed with the reasons for it.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
(i) Make sure to have administrator permissions for the space in question.

# Go to an existing personal space;
# Tap the *Space settings* at the sidebar;
# Take note of the space's creator and select *Permissions*;
# Tap *Edit* and toggle any of the permissions from the owner (to remove them);
# *Save* the performed changes;

h3. Expected Results
A message clarifying why it can't be removed should be displayed.

h3. Actual Results
Nothing happens. The page is refreshed and the owner permissions are in the same state.

h3. Workaround
Currently, there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

h3. Issue Summary
When we add a *Contributors* macro within a *Page Properties* one, pulling this info on another page with the *Page Properties Report* macro will show the respective information regarding the *Contributors* macro only once after editing the page.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a page;
# Add the *Page Properties* macro;
# Add a table and name one of the headers as _Contributor_;
# On the respective cell to _Contributor_ header, call the */contributors* macro;
# Add a label to this page and publish it (the label needs to be set so then you can call it in the report);
# Create a new page;
# Add the *Page Properties Report* macro;
# Set it to call pages with the label you set on the previous page;
# Publish the page (it shows the contributor, right?)
# Navigate to another page and then get back to the one you added the report.

h3. Expected Results
The contributor's name is still being shown.

h3. Actual Results
The name is gone

*Notes*:
* Accessing the editing mode of the page that contains the report and then backing to the published mode will show the name once.

h3. Workaround
Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

h3. Issue Summary

Finnish keyboard (probably also other scandinavian keyboards) doesn't handle ` for markdown shortcut correctly. This bug also applies to Jira and probably Bitbucket as they use the same editor.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # In editor or comments type `foo` using Finnish keyboard layout to get inline code *foo*

h3. Expected Results
{code:java}
foo{code}
h3. Actual Results
{noformat}
`oo{noformat}
h3. Workaround

Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

h3. Issue Summary

When viewing a code block that contains Sass or SCSS code, the code is not highlighted after selecting the "Sass" option from the dropdown and publishing the page.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Edit a page
 # Add a code block
 # Select "Sass" from the language dropdown
 # Insert the following Sass or SCSS code:
{code:css}
/* Sass example */
/* This CSS will print because %message-shared is extended. */
%message-shared
  border: 1px solid #ccc
  padding: 10px
  color: #333


// This CSS won't print because %equal-heights is never extended.
%equal-heights
  display: flex
  flex-wrap: wrap


.message
  @extend %message-shared {code}
{code:css}
/* SCSS example */
/* This CSS will print because %message-shared is extended. */
%message-shared {
  border: 1px solid #ccc;
  padding: 10px;
  color: #333;
}

// This CSS won't print because %equal-heights is never extended.
%equal-heights {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.message {
  @extend %message-shared;
}{code}

 # Publish the page

h3. Expected Results

Published page shows syntax-highlighted code block
h3. Actual Results

Published page shows a code block with no syntax highlighting
!image-2020-07-01-00-07-52-300.png|width=944,height=447!
h3. Workaround

Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

h3. Issue Summary
When using the /rest/api/content/search endpoint to look for pages with a certain parent, if there're around 300 results or more, the request will fail.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
* Create a page tree with 300 pages under the same parent
* Get the parent page's ID and perform the following GET request:
{code:none}https://INSTANCE.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/search?cql=parent=PAGE_ID{code}

h3. Expected Results
It should return all the pages with that parent page

h3. Actual Results
It responds with a 400 and the following error:
{code:none}{
statusCode: 400,
data: {
authorized: false,
valid: true,
errors: [ ],
successful: false
},
message: "com.atlassian.confluence.api.service.exceptions.BadRequestException: CQL was parsed but the search manager was unable to execute the search. CQL: 'parent=33719082'. Error message: ElasticsearchException[SearchPhaseExecutionException[all shards failed]]"
}{code}

h3. Workaround
Use the /content/ endpoint instead:
{code:none}https://INSTANCE.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/PAGE_ID/child/page?limit=1000&start=0{code}
